Subject: [PATCH 2/2] gflags: use static explicitly

kept on failing regardless of if only static was installed due to
shlwapi not being set as a link target for some reason, can't figure out
why because I can't put more effort into this

Signed-off-by: Christopher Degawa <ccom@randomderp.com>
---
 third_party/CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/third_party/CMakeLists.txt b/third_party/CMakeLists.txt
index 9c0be83..fcab826 100644
--- a/third_party/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/third_party/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -165,7 +165,7 @@ if (JPEGXL_BUNDLE_GFLAGS)
                  ${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR}/LICENSE.gflags COPYONLY)
 else()
   # Use sytem libgflags-dev
-  find_package(gflags REQUIRED)
+  find_package(gflags REQUIRED COMPONENTS static)
   if (NOT gflags_FOUND)
     message(FATAL_ERROR
       "Gflags not found, install libgflags-dev or download gflags source to"
